name: js-applyunary-effect-cps
backends: [int, js]
---

# unary operator on an effectful operand is CPS-lowered (JS backend)

Regression for the JS backend (busi deep-offline standalone bundle, surfaced by
`tests/v2/trust.ssc`). A unary operator (`!x`, `-x`, `~x`, `+x`) whose operand
is effectful (here `total()` transitively performs `Box.read`) fell through to
the non-CPS `genExpr`, which `_run`-wrapped the operand — running the effect
*outside* the enclosing handler (`Unhandled effect` / wrong value). `genCpsExpr`
now binds the operand first (`_bind(<operand>, v => op(v))`), keeping the effect
inside the handler.

[runBox, query, Acc](./lib/effect-box.ssc)

```scalascript
def total(): Int = query(0, Acc(0, (s, x) => s + x))

println(runBox(() => -total()))
println(runBox(() => !(total() == 6)))
```
